<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-654-814  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 654 814.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Educational Technology  July 1990 v30 n7 p57(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Educational technology product reviews: HyperCALL 1.0: HyperCardcomputer-assisted language learning. (Software Review )(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Fox, Hugh B.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>HyperCALL, $39.95 from Kinko's Service Corp, Academic CoursewareExchange was developed as an aid for language instructorsproducing CALL (computer-assisted language learning) materials forthe Apple Computer Macintosh.andP;  Using HyperCALL stretches thecapabilities of HyperCard by taking advantage of HyerCard'sability to include external commands from other sources.andP;  Theprogram is very user friendly and well documented, but usersshould have some experience authoring HyperCard stacks.andP;  Theprogram is weak in instructional management.andP;  Teachers who createHyperCard stacks will find HyperCALL valuable, but may want towait until the next version which is supposed to have an animationcommand button, a student activity log, and a VCR tape driver.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Kinko's Service Corp. (products).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (computer programs)HyperCALL (Computer program).andO;Topic:     TeachingComputer-Assisted InstructionEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>